post_text:
Stafford County Public Schools (SCPS), in partnership with Stafford County Fire and Rescue and the Stafford Education Foundation, will host a fundraiser to support Operation Warm at the Augustine Golf Club on Saturday, September 26, from 11 a.m. – 5 p.m.

During this event, the golf club will donate $4 for every bucket of balls used on the driving range and $10 for every round of golf played to Operation Warm. For every $20 raised, Operation Warm provides a child in need with a new winter coat. This year, SCPS has a $15,000 fundraising goal.

See you on the green!

post_text: In only its third year, the Mountain View High School (MVHS) Marine Corps Junior Reserve Officers’ Training Corps (MCJROTC) program has won the Marine Corps Reserve Association (MCRA) Award for the 2019-2020 school year. There are 268 MCJROTC programs worldwide currently divided among four regions. The MCRA recognizes the most outstanding MCJROTC unit in each MCJROTC region.

post_text:
Today is the last day to apply to become a member of the Equity Diversity and Opportunity Committee (EDOC)!

EDOC acts as an advisory arm to the SCPS Office of Equity by providing additional information, ideas, and support regarding matters of equity, diversity, and inclusion in our schools. EDOC, like the SCPS Office of Equity, exists to ensure equity prevails in SCPS, and that all students and staff are valued and affirmed.

Visit https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/EDOC to apply before the close of business.

post_text: As a reminder, Friday, September 4, and Monday, September 7, 2020 are Stafford County Public School holidays. As such, no meal service will be available on these dates. Today is National Just Because Day, a time to do anything you want just because.

Join the Equity Diversity and Opportunity Committee (EDOC)!

EDOC acts as an advisory arm to the SCPS Office of Equity by providing additional information, ideas, and support regarding matters of equity, diversity, and inclusion in our schools. EDOC, like the SCPS Office of Equity, exists to ensure equity prevails in SCPS, and that all students and staff are valued and affirmed.

Visit https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/EDOC to apply. The deadline for submissions is the close of business on September 4, 2020.

Stafford County Public Schools would like to thank the community for its overwhelming response to the Superintendent’s request for face masks. If you would like to create and donate masks, please see the guidelines provided by the Centers for Disease Control. https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/how-to-make-cloth-face-covering.html

SCPS will distribute masks to schools on August 4 as part of its Collect for Kids campaign. Community members may drop off donated masks at any Collect for Kids donation site, or mail completed masks to Stafford County Public Schools, ATTN: Communications, 31 Stafford Ave, Stafford, VA 22554. https://www.staffordschools.net/collectforkids

SCPS does not provide supplies to create the masks. Please place masks in a sealed plastic bag before placing in donation bins or mailing. Thank you for generously supporting our students and staff. #SCPSCollectForKids

Stafford Education Foundation
June 1 at 5:16 PM ·

Innovative Teaching Grant (ITG) applications are due in just two weeks! ITGs are designed to provide teachers with the opportunity to improve student achievement and learning through innovative and creative practices. post_text: Every year Hampton Oaks Elementary School hosts a Hawk House Cup Celebration. It is normally kicked off by the Seniors that once were Hampton Oaks Elementary Hawks coming down to the school and walking in caps and gowns through the hallways. The 5th graders get to walk with them and then meet with some of the Seniors who talk about the Strong Effort it took to get to where they are at. This year current and former hawks adapted for a Virtual Senior and 5th Grade walk. #StrongerTogether #StrongerTogether2020 #SCPSStrong #SCPSStayEngaged

post_text: Mrs. Susan Weiderhold, an Assistant Principal at Dixon-Smith Middle School, is one of only 10 educators nationwide to earn a Rebecca Burnette DuFour Scholarship. This award, now in its second year, celebrates and supports women educators who demonstrate exceptional leadership in their school communities. Weiderhold has 26 years of experience in education as a teacher, instructional coach, and administrator. Her dedication to educational research and learning led Weiderhold to find the Professional Learning Community (PLC) practice, founded by the DuFours, that resulted in immeasurable gains for student learning and confidence. As a result, she now leads a staff that continues to build their own capacity in the PLC process. In the past four years, Weiderhold’s leadership has helped create a climate that advances teacher understanding and promotes student-centered learning across all grade levels. #SCPSStrong #SCPSStayEngaged

post_text:
The Washington Post Educational Foundation's SCPS Teacher of the Year finalists included Mrs. Kimberly Cannon, sixth-grade science teacher at Stafford Middle School.

Cannon approaches engaging and effective instruction
through the lens of a child sitting in a classroom. Cannon’s lessons incorporate exciting activities that reinforce learning,
such as simulations. As the sixth-grade lead teacher, she ensures her colleagues are moving forward with a clear
understanding of school procedures and communicates her ideas with ease and confidence. Cannon has presented at the
Leadership Learning Exchange and the Response to Intervention (RTI) Convention. She participated in the Social Studies Assessment Consortium, the RTI Coalition, and was awarded the Initiatives in Education Grant. #SCPSStrong #SCPSStayEngaged
